<TITLE> Tarique gets new passport </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com)BNP senior joint secretary general Tarique Rahman received a new passport on Thursday, his lawyer advocate Ahmed Azam Khan told bdnews24.com. A second lawyer Nasiruddin Ashim said that preparations were on to take the BNP leader to the UK or Germany as soon as possible for better medical treatment. "Tarique's passport, visa and so on are being taken care of, so that he can fly out to the UK or Germany as soon as doctors permit and travel formalities are fulfilled," Ashim told bdnews24.com earlier in the day. A medical board convened at BSMMU Hospital Thursday morinrg, meanwhile, advised two days of complete bed rest for the elder son of still-detained BNP chief and former prime minister Khaleda Zia. Shamsur Rahman Shimul Biswas, another of Tarique's lawyers, told bdnews24.com: "We are making preparations to fly Tarique out as soon as possible for better treatment, as further advised by doctors." bdnew
